 A man and a woman died when their car launched over the N2 bridge, near the M25 Kwa-Mashu off-ramp, in Durban, on Sunday.Netcare 911’s Shawn Herbst said reports indicate that the driver of an SUV lost control, resulting in the vehicle crashing through the safety barriers, down an embankment about fifteen metres, coming to rest on railway tracks below.“When medics arrived on scene, they found that the occupants had been thrown from the vehicle.”  On assessment, medics found that a man and a woman had died from their injuries.“The third patient, an adult male, had sustained moderate to serious injuries and was treated on scene before being transported by ambulance to hospital for further care.”  •